               <p>JOHN JOY. I am a <rs id="t18270913-383-viclabel2119" type="occupation">plasterer's labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-383-victim2705 t18270913-383-viclabel2119"></join>. On the 22d of August, at half-past four o'clock, I lost my jacket from <placeName id="t18270913-383-crimeloc2120">Belgrave-place, Pimlico</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-383-crimeloc2120" type="placeName" value="Belgrave-place, Pimlico"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-383-crimeloc2120" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-383-off2117 t18270913-383-crimeloc2120"></join>, while I was gone to tea - I saw the prisoner with it on, on the 13th of September - he had it on inside his waistcoat - he said it was his own, but I am certain of it - he said he bought it twelve months ago in a public-house; I am quite certain it is mine - there is a hole in the right-hand pocket, and two marks on the shoulder, where I carry my hod, and some oil spilt on the right sleeve.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-383-person2706">
                  JOHN 
                  SUTHERLAND
               <interp inst="t18270913-383-person2706" type="surname" value="SUTHERLAND"></interp>
