                     <interp inst="t18270913-383-person2706" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was called and took the prisoner with the jacket on - he said it was his own - I said it was rather tight - he said he bought in a public-house in Westminster, but could not tell what he gave for it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I wish him to try it on (the prosecutor did so, and it appeared to fit him) - the Magistrate said if I would give it up I might go.</p>
               <p>JOHN SUTHERLAND. That is not true.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 37.</p>
